{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἐγγύς</b> [ῠ], <br /> <i>adverb</i>, <i>comparative</i> ἐγγυτέρω (-τέρῳ[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Hellenica Oxyrhynchia” 6.3), also -ύτερον 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 704e: _superlative_ ἐγγυτάτω\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] or -ύτατα (first in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus, and _Attic dialect_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also ἔγγῑον, ἔγγιστα (see. ἐγγίων). <br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> of Place, <b>near, nigh, at hand</b>: frequently in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus, ἐ. γὰρ νυκτός τε καὶ ἤματός εἰσι κέλευθοι 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 10.86 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>genitive</i>, <b>hard by, near to</b>; so λύπας ἐγγυτέρω <b>nearer to</b> grief, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 1217: with _dative_, 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 11.340, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Heraclidae” 37 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἐγγὺς ὁδῷ uncertain in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 12.974: mostly with Verbs of rest, ἐ. ἑστάναι, παρεστάναι, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 686, “Eu.” 65; but ἐ. χωρεῖν [prev. author] “Th.” 59: with _genitive_, οἱ ἐγγυτάτω τῆς ἀγορᾶς κατεσκευασμένοι 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 24.20, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> of Time, <b>nigh at hand</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 22.453; ἐ. ἡμῖν ὁ ἀγών 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 2.3.2. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> of Numbers, etc., <b>nearly</b>, ἔτεσι ἐ. εἴκοσι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.5; μισθὸς ἐ. ἐνιαυτοῦ 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 3.1.28 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: generally, <b>nearly, almost</b>, ἐ. ἔγνως [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ichn.” 301 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οὐδ᾽ ἐ. τινος not <b>nearly</b>, i. e. not <b>by a great deal</b>, nothing <b>like</b> it, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 198b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἔχει οὐχ οὕτω ταῦτα οὐδ᾽ ἐ. not so.. nor yet <b>nearly so</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.30; οὐκ ἐποίουν τοῦτο, οὐδ᾽ ἐ. [prev. author] 18.96 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <b>mostly</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “Mochl.” 34. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> of Qualities, <b>coming near</b>, ἐ. τι καὶ παραπλήσιον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 520a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐγγύτατα τοῦ νῦν τρόπου, τῆς ξυμπάσης γνώμης, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.13, 22; ὅτι ἐγγύτατα τούτων [prev. author] 7.86; κοινῇ δὲ πᾶσιν οὐδεὶς ἐγγυτέρω 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.288; δοκεῖς δηλῶσαι ἐγγύτατα τὴν ῥητορικήν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 452e \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐ. εἶναι, with <i>genitive</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Phd.” 116b; ἐ. τυφλῶν [prev. author] “R.” 508c \">Refs</a>]; ἐ. τι τείνειν τοῦ τεθνάναι <b>very near</b> death, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Phd.” 65a; κακῶς παθεῖν ἐγγύτατα 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.123. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__V</b></Level2> of Relationship, <b>akin to</b>, οἱ Ζηνὸς ἐ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Fragmenta - American Journal of Philology” 162 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ἐγγυτέρω γένει or γένους, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Apologia” 30a, 4th c.BC: Isaeus Orator 3.72; ἐγγύτατα γένους 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 388, 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator “Fragmenta” 41, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Hp.Ma.” 304d; ἐγγυτάτω γένους “IG” 12.77, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 1666. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G1451","accentedUnicode":"ἐγγύς","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G1448","matchingForm":"ἐγγίζω","stepTransliteration":"engizō","gloss":"to come near","_zh_tw_Gloss":"近了","_es_Gloss":"acercarse ","_zh_Gloss":"近了"},{"strongNumber":"G1452","matchingForm":"ἐγγύτερος","stepTransliteration":"enguteros","gloss":"nearer","_zh_tw_Gloss":"更近了","_es_Gloss":"más cerca ","_zh_Gloss":"更近了"}],"shortDef":"near, close","mediumDef":"near, close <br />some view as an <i>improper preposition</i>, followed by <i>genitive</i> or <i>dative</i>, <b>near,</b> as to place, <ref='Luk.19.11'>Lk. 19:11</ref>; <b>close at hand,</b> <ref='Rom.10.8'>Rom. 10:8;</ref> <b>near,</b> in respect of ready interposition, <ref='Php.4.5'>Phil. 4:5;</ref> <b>near,</b> as to time, <ref='Mat.24.32, 33'>Mt. 24:32, 33</ref>; <b>near</b> to God, as being in covenant with him, <ref='Eph.2.13'>Eph. 2:13;</ref> <greek>οἱ ἐγγύς</greek>, <b>the people near</b> to God, the Jews, <ref='Eph.2.17'>Eph. 2:17</ref>","stepGloss":"near","stepTransliteration":"engus","count":30,"_es_Definition":"adv. cerca, junto a ; a punto de","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) (空間上的) 靠近<br>2) (時間上的) 臨近<br>3) (經驗與事件) 近於","_zh_Definition":"1) (空间上的) 靠近<br>2) (时间上的) 临近<br>3) (经验与事件) 近于","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"gần; gần kề","_zh_tw_Gloss":"近了","_es_Gloss":"cerca ","_zh_Gloss":"近了"}]}